      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The Fernie yard have a strong hand here led by the talented WHATYOUTALKINBOUT (2). Three start galloper who was a maiden winner here two back then just missed this class before a break. Has upside and expected to go close. Stablemate GIBRALTAR GOLD (1) looks the main danger and is also resuming. Has two wins and two minors here at home and is a fresh-up winner. Suited this class and drawn for a soft run. BONDI'S SON (6) has been racing in richer company and looks well placed here with the low draw and the claim. Placed this course and distance and gets chance to find best form. MYSTICAL WISDOM (4) is a former SA galloper who has had two runs for the new yard and resumes from a break. One of the chances. GUARD THE MULLAH (3) has been thereabouts lately and drawn to feature.",
